Use the standard library
This is how to hex_key of num:
   Remember that count is 0
   Remember that keys is "0123456789ABCDEF"
   Remember that n is num's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that c is item i in num
      When c is in keys, then:
         Increase count
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is count
Now you know
>>> hex_key of [65, 66] 
1
>>> hex_key of [49, 48, 55, 55, 69] 
2
>>> hex_key of [65, 66, 69, 68, 49, 65, 51, 51] 
4